Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.05,0:00:02.51,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.75,0:00:05.68,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.85,0:00:14.89,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Masato Suzuki, the producer at Green\NBunny told our company, ARMS, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.96,0:00:24.90,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...he knew of an eccentric creator and\Nwanted to make an animation with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.97,0:00:31.81,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,We actually had planned\Nanother animation once and...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.37,0:00:31.01,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,{\fscx120\pos(386.23,410.4)}Producer: Osamu Koshinaka
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.84,0:00:37.88,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...asked Mr. Umetsu. Unfortunately\Nthat plan didn't work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.95,0:00:44.69,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Years after that happened, we\Napproached Mr. Umetsu again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.82,0:00:51.16,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,When we asked him, he told us\Nthat he had an idea for a project.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.36,0:00:55.77,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,That's how we started\Nproducing "A Kite".
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.14,0:01:08.61,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,He was very tough\Nwhen we were working.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.85,0:01:13.89,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,He made people around him\Nwork like they were in hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.95,0:01:22.19,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,But we knew that for his film,\Nit would be worth the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.36,0:01:30.00,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,The staff listened to whatever he\Nwanted and tried to get closer to...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.10,0:01:32.57,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...the images he had in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.70,0:01:36.21,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,He is one of the few\Ncreators who has a power...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.31,0:01:39.78,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...to make the staff feel like\Nthey want to work harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.85,0:01:44.98,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I thought he was very talented,\Nfun to work with, and also...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.15,0:01:49.59,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...he could create an animation\Nthat would satisfy the staff...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.65,0:01:52.06,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...when it was completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.06,0:01:55.53,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Well, the schedule management\Nwas the most difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.56,0:02:00.33,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,The director had specific and\Nclear images in his mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.40,0:02:05.67,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...so he was never satisfied until\Nhe got exactly what he wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.74,0:02:10.21,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,We had to balance between\Nthe schedule and the budget...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.31,0:02:16.88,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,It required us to choose\Nwhich one had priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.95,0:02:21.59,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,But the director stuck to what\Nhe wanted until the last minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.62,0:02:27.66,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,So some staffers always had to stay up\Nall night to catch up with the schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.73,0:02:30.76,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,This happens a lot in\Nthis business but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.86,0:02:38.97,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,He finished the piece after being worn\Nout from staying up all night for days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.10,0:02:45.58,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,The last minute struggle was\Nreflected in the finished piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.68,0:02:56.72,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,There were things I couldn't do anything\Nabout because of the schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.82,0:03:03.73,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,As a producer, I still have a sense\Nof bitterness with "A Kite".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.73,0:03:10.57,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,We spent a lot of time\Nbefore shooting started.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.60,0:03:13.71,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Mr. Umetsu ate it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.87,0:03:18.04,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,He ate all of the schedule including\Nother people's schedules...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.14,0:03:23.68,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,We started shooting behind schedule\Nbut the deadline stayed the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.78,0:03:30.56,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,He did as much as he wanted and that's\Nwhy the piece was successful but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.62,0:03:32.89,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,He stuck and stuck to his ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.96,0:03:39.06,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I understood that he\Nwanted to do more but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.13,0:03:42.43,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...I had to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.50,0:03:44.17,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,That was my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.24,0:03:51.24,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,If we could, we would spend more money\Nand time to go on with the details...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.54,0:03:55.58,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,But I think the piece would be boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.75,0:03:59.82,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Mr. Umetsu and I always had\Ndiscussions on the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.02,0:04:02.92,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I think it's the same\Nthing with all producers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.92,0:04:07.73,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,What Mr. Umetsu and I did...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.83,0:04:12.03,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Mr. Umetsu worked on the content\Nof the piece almost 100 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.16,0:04:16.60,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,And we tried to make it as\Nclose to his image as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.67,0:04:23.24,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,What I cared about was the\Nrepresentation of that in animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.38,0:04:30.38,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,There are things you can do in\Nboth live action and animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.42,0:04:32.42,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,But basically, it was an animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.48,0:04:37.49,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I told him once that I wanted him\Nto care about things that were...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.56,0:04:41.29,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...only possible to\Nrepresent in animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.36,0:04:42.46,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,That was it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.56,0:04:47.47,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Everything else was under\NMr. Umetsu's control.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.53,0:04:51.07,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I tried to work in compliance\Nwith what he wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.68,0:05:07.32,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I think animation shouldn't have violent\Nscenes if it is going to be on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.32,0:05:12.69,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,This would make it an X-rated\Nanimation from the beginning...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.79,0:05:17.60,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...there wasn't any problem\Nwith that in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.83,0:05:21.90,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,{\fscx120\pos(386.23,410.4)}Producer: Osamu Koshinaka
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.20,0:05:22.67,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,But the way children are not allowed\Nto see violence in the U.S....
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.77,0:05:26.37,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,When I was in the U.S., I saw\Na movie with a violent scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.44,0:05:28.84,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,There were six black frames\Nand right after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.94,0:05:31.91,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...a man who got hit was\Nflying through the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.98,0:05:34.75,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.81,0:05:39.62,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Children can tell it's there\Neven though they can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.72,0:05:41.32,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,It's noticeable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.42,0:05:45.22,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,In fact, the U.S. still\Nhas a high crime rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.42,0:05:50.03,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,The violent scenes should be shown...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.10,0:05:58.70,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...carefully based on the\Ncreators' criteria or aesthetics.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.80,0:06:02.91,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,From the creator's point of view...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.01,0:06:08.08,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...it is wrong to ban all\Nthe violent scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.41,0:06:12.48,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,The main reason is marketing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:19.96,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,By putting sexual scenes, we are\Nassured that we'll have a certain market.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.29,0:06:27.30,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Including those scenes was\Na condition we had to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.40,0:06:34.04,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,The Japanese animation industry\Nwouldn't let Mr. Umetsu...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.14,0:06:38.51,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...create freely without the condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.51,0:06:40.01,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,It's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.15,0:06:49.45,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Since he wants very realistic brutal\Nscenes, like a severed head rolling around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.55,0:06:59.50,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Those necessary things for him as\Nan artist are not allowed on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.60,0:07:07.74,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he'll receive recognition\Nbecause of his talent, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.84,0:07:13.14,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...there weren't any producers\Nwho would let him create.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.24,0:07:17.78,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,So in that sense, we\Nhad a better chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.25,0:07:30.73,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,The movies that I like? I like anime and\Nthat why I'm in the anime industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.86,0:07:34.27,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,But in terms of movies, I\Nlike old American films.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.43,0:07:40.91,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Old movies like "High Noon",\N"Shane" and "Roman Holiday".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.07,0:07:47.48,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,In terms of animations, I really\Nlike Japanese animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.65,0:07:55.32,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,In recent works, I was impressed\Nby Disney's "Tarzan and Jane".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.79,0:08:04.63,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Disney and Japanese\Nanimation are totally different.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.76,0:08:09.20,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I liked Disney's old animation\Nlike "101 Dalmatians" but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.73,0:08:10.74,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,{\fscx120\pos(386.23,410.4)}Producer: Osamu Koshinaka
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.27,0:08:11.97,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...I didn't like their new works.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.04,0:08:17.81,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I was amazed by the imagination\Nin "Tarzan and Jane".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.91,0:08:25.48,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,There are many talented creators in\NJapan, so we have been creating...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.58,0:08:29.15,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...stimulating animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.42,0:08:34.43,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,But personally, I'm influenced by\Nanimations from my childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.79,0:08:44.20,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Like, "Gatchaman", "Casshern"\Nand "Tiger Mask"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.27,0:08:48.04,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I saw them when I was\Nin elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.11,0:08:51.91,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,And of course, "Space Battleship\NYamato" and "Umino Toriton"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.98,0:08:57.18,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,That's when I started becoming\Nan "animation Otaku".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.18,0:09:00.99,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I haven't been planning for this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.05,0:09:03.76,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,...I want to make\Nanimations for children.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.89,0:09:18.14,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,A boy or girl's adventure animation\Nfor kids around age 7 to 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.34,0:09:22.51,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I'm hoping that I will be able to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.51,0:09:30.78,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,It's because I don't get to do\Nthose type of animations often.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.88,0:09:34.75,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I always get bloody\Nand erotic animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.85,0:09:40.22,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I want the challenge of doing\Nsomething completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.67,0:09:59.91,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,It seems like "A Kite" will be produced\Nas a live action in Hollywood movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.04,0:10:03.82,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Also, Yasuomi Umetsu produces\Nother interesting works.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.88,0:10:07.72,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,I know there are many\Namazing animations in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.79,0:10:12.52,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Mr. Umetsu and I always\Ncreate interesting work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.59,0:10:17.33,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,We'll continue making anime, hoping\Nmany people will be able to see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.43,0:10:20.57,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Please support Yasuomi Umetsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.23,0:10:24.67,Hardsub,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
